Introduction¶

Americas first marketplace lending platform, with over $9 billion in funded loans. This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan.

What is the structure of data?¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

What the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I saw in this data, the main feature that interest in data is BorrowerAPR or Borrower rate.

Another interesting variable is the prosper score, This information can be used to build a predictive model for risk management in bank or financial.

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

BorrowerAPR or Borrower rate and this feature may affected by EmployeeStatus, loan amount, prosper rate, prosper score.

Distribute Relation Between BorrowerAPR, ProsperRating (Alpha)

The plot show strong correlation between the prosper rating/score with the borrowers APR. where Prosper Rating is assigned at the time the listing was created between AA - HR. Applicable for loans originated after July 2009.

The plot show strong correlation between the prosper rating/score with the borrowers APR. where Prosper Score A custom risk score built using historical Prosper data. The score ranges from 1-10, with 10 being the best, or lowest risk score. Applicable for loans originated after July 2009 so if score is high that mean lower BorrowerAPR so Loan can be big.
